commit.message:
Replace pyparsing with regular expressions

This is a reimplementation of the svgwrite.data.svgparser module based on
the re standard module. The test cases have been adjusted and pyparsing
have been removed as a dependency.

test_parsing_basic_types no longer checks all different sub types of
numbers as they are no longer exposed separately. These test cases have
been commented out.

The new code no longer is compatible with Python 2 due to the use of
modern string formatting.
raise required Python version to 3.6

commit.message:
Use re module for data.svgparser.is_valid_pathdata()

This is some orders of magnitude faster than pyparsing
Add test for path parsing performance

ignore svg tag at pretty print testing

Order of svg attribute of the svg tag has changed in Python 3.8,
ignoring this tag is the easiest way to solve this problem.
